# Sprint 19 / TLC-035 — EOL normalization
#
# Forces LF line endings in the repository regardless of host OS, with
# auto-conversion for text files. Eliminates EOL-induced rebase drift
# that Sprint 18 PR #10 + #12 hit on Windows-host autonomous shell
# (Windows defaults `core.autocrlf=true` → CRLF in working copy → LF
# stored in repo → prettier on Windows sees CRLF and warns even when
# repo content is correct).
#
# Sprint 18 retro proposed TLC-035 as the codified fix; landed in
# Sprint 19 alongside TLC-034 advisory-lock fix because rebases of
# the TLC-034 PR would themselves trigger the same EOL drift this
# file prevents.
#
# Spec references:
#   - docs/SPRINT_18_RETRO.md "Process changes for Sprint 19" (TLC-035
#     candidate proposed)
#   - docs/SPRINT_19_PLAN.md (this sprint)
#
# All text files default to auto-detected text + LF in repo.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Source/test files explicitly LF (defensive — covers extensions that
# auto-detection might misclassify on certain platforms).
*.ts text eol=lf
*.tsx text eol=lf
*.js text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.sql text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf

# Binary files — disable text conversion outright.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
